01:10.459 --> 01:11.769
<i>It's been four months</i>

01:11.794 --> 01:14.576
<i>since little Jack Thornton was born.</i>

01:15.754 --> 01:19.692
<i>In that time I've learned that
motherhood is a lot of work</i>

01:19.717 --> 01:23.453
<i>but it also fills you
with profound joyous</i>

01:23.478 --> 01:25.544
<i>and unfettered love.</i>

01:26.915 --> 01:28.599
<i>I've also learned that
little Jack shares</i>

01:28.624 --> 01:31.551
<i>certain characteristics with his father.</i>

01:31.902 --> 01:35.262
<i>The women of Hope Valley
thoroughly enjoy his company</i>

01:35.918 --> 01:38.265
<i>and the men want to be his friend.</i>

01:39.364 --> 01:42.219
<i>As glorious as the past
few months have been,</i>

01:42.244 --> 01:44.347
<i>this week I've been faced
with the necessary task</i>

01:44.372 --> 01:46.255
<i>of returning to work.</i>

01:46.496 --> 01:49.599
<i>Little Jack isn't the only
child who depends on me,</i>

01:49.679 --> 01:52.248
<i>and now, as a single mother,</i>

01:52.273 --> 01:55.784
<i>my calling and my livelihood
take on greater meaning.</i>

01:56.301 --> 01:58.786
<i>It breaks my heart to be
away from my darling boy.</i>

01:59.334 --> 02:01.323
<i>Fortunately, my friends
have created a schedule</i>

02:01.348 --> 02:04.709
<i>that always leaves little Jack
in someone's loving arms.</i>

02:07.711 --> 02:11.474
<i>With everyone's help I'm hopeful
that I can balance work</i>

02:11.499 --> 02:14.870
<i>with the joy and responsibility
of raising my child.</i>

02:14.895 --> 02:16.220
Come in.

02:16.245 --> 02:17.411
Good morning.

02:17.436 --> 02:19.266
Good morning, Florence.

02:19.955 --> 02:21.731
Good, you have a bottle ready.

02:21.756 --> 02:25.864
I just love you so, so,
so, so, so, so, so much.

02:27.989 --> 02:29.191
Ohhh.

02:30.778 --> 02:32.361
Elizabeth?

02:33.718 --> 02:36.685
And when I come home I'm going
to bathe you and feed you

02:36.710 --> 02:41.622
and read to you and...
oh yes, and kiss you.

02:41.647 --> 02:43.282
It's only your second day back.

02:43.307 --> 02:45.250
You don't want to be late.

02:48.846 --> 02:50.283
Alright.

02:53.442 --> 02:54.910
Say goodbye to mommy.

02:55.092 --> 02:57.054
He will be fine.

02:57.636 --> 02:59.271
I promise.

03:09.549 --> 03:12.943
Oh, yes, you're such a lovely boy.

03:16.834 --> 03:18.479
Ok.

03:22.720 --> 03:24.589
I thought she'd never leave.

03:24.614 --> 03:27.459
We're gonna talk about
everybody in town.

03:41.073 --> 03:47.521
- Synced and corrected by martythecrazy -
